I had the same problem with these files. Just do what I did:

1)  Select the file with the extension ".001" and right-click it. 
2)  Select "Open" and "Choose a program from a list" from the menu.
3)  Select "WinRar" and then "OK".
4)  Extract the newly created .avi file to any folder you wish and use the appropriate player to view.

Hope this helps.

No need to rename these files! 

This may cause extracting problems and is not necessary to do so. Just open with WinRar for best results.
